                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/311.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="122" xml:id="d1418fn122">Similar telegram to the American Consul
                        General at Monterey.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Spanish Ambassador, this city, reports that Constitutionalists at Monterey are
                    levying discriminatory taxes against Spaniards and making unfounded arrests for
                    purpose of demanding ransom from Spaniards.</p>
                <p>Bring to attention of Carranza and urge that no discriminatory or confiscatory
                    action be taken against property of Spaniards and that they be not arrested
                    without good cause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
